result.execSummary:
The defendant Jarrett J Michalowski was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Robbery with Use of Force [Modifiers: Party to a Crime], a class E felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.32(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

superMiscConds.notes: $400.00 to be paid to Jeffrey S. FIRST before all costs, fees and surcharges.

Provide a DNA sample; pay surcharge (unless previously paid). Pay all costs, fees and surcharges including restitution surcharge. Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment. Court costs, fees, and surcharges and restitution be paid through collection by the DOC's from 25% of funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b) and as a condition of ES.

Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon he may never possess any gun or other firearms. Court advised defendant that his voting rights are suspended, and may not vote in any election until his civil rights are restored.

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:
- Maintain absolute sobriety.
- Random urine screens.
- Present valid prescription to agent BEFORE filling it.
- Obtain/maintain full-time employment of at least 30 hours per week. If not employed full-time, be enrolled in vocational training.
- Obtain HSED.
- No Contact with the victim or Nikki P.

records.addlTxt: Original Transcript SENTENCING HEARING (34 pages) commencing AUGUST 11, 2015 received and filed.

Defendant Jarrett J Michalowski in court with attorney Scott F. Anderson.  Defendant Jarrett J Michalowski in custody.  Sara Nicole Volden Schroeder appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Deputy court clerk ccp.
Case set for Jury Trial. Parties have reached a resolution in this matter. State placed negotiations on the record. Victim Impact Statement received and filed. Plea hearing proceeded.
Defendant sworn in.

As to COUNT 1 as AMENDED-
Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, and plead GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights, Addendum, and Jury Instructions received and filed.  Stipulation by parties to the Criminal Complaint as a factual basis to sustain the plea.  Court found the defendant guilty.  Judgment of conviction entered.
  
Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon he may never possess any gun or other firearms. 
Court advised defendant that his voting rights are suspended, and may not vote in any election until his civil rights are restored.  

Court advised defendant if he is not a citizen of the United States of America, that upon a plea of guilty or no contest for this offense, he could be deported, excluded from admission to his country, or denied naturalization under federal law.  
Court advised that the defendant will have to provide a DNA sample, to the Wisconsin State Crime Laboratory for DNA testing and pay a DNA surcharge.

State requests an adjourned scheduling date for purposes of victim notification. Court granted State's request. Case adjourned to Branch 25.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for August 11, 2015 at 01:30 pm.
